        'Journalist who will definitely ask you a lot of questions on our first date - it''s an occupational hazard. I cover tech and startups, which means I''m constantly learning about new things and meeting interesting people. I got into journalism because I''m endlessly curious about how the world works. I''m looking for someone who has stories to tell, opinions to share, and doesn''t mind being interviewed over drinks. I promise the article won''t be about you.',
        'Social worker with a dark sense of humor - it''s how I cope with the heavy stuff I deal with at work. I spend my days helping families in crisis, which is incredibly rewarding but also emotionally exhausting. I need someone who can help me decompress, who doesn''t take everything too seriously, and who understands that sometimes I just need to watch trashy TV and not think about anything important.',
        'Bartender who can make you the perfect cocktail for any mood. I''ve been doing this for eight years and I''ve learned to read people pretty well. I love the theater of a good bar - the drinks, the atmosphere, the conversations with strangers at 2am. I work nights and weekends, so my schedule is weird, but I promise I''m worth the calendar gymnastics. Looking for someone who appreciates a well-crafted drink and isn''t afraid of a late-night date.',
        'UX designer who thinks your dating profile could use some work - but I''ll help you fix it. I spend my days making apps easier to use, and I can''t help but apply that thinking to everything, including relationships. I believe good design is about understanding people and their needs. I''m looking for someone who pays attention to details, who can give and receive feedback well, and who understands that great things take iteration.',
        'Musician seeking someone to harmonize with - literally and figuratively. I play multiple instruments and I''m in two different bands right now, which keeps me pretty busy. Music is my first love, but I have room in my heart for more. I''m looking for someone who appreciates live music, doesn''t mind late-night gigs, and might even let me write a song about them if things go well.',
        'Photographer looking for my next muse - and maybe something more. I shoot mostly portraits and street photography, and I''m always looking for interesting faces and stories. My apartment is full of prints and photo books, and my camera is basically an extension of my arm. Looking for someone who''s comfortable in front of the camera, or at least willing to be photographed occasionally for my Instagram.',
        'Dancer with moves both on and off the dance floor. I''ve been dancing since I was five and it''s still my favorite way to express myself. I teach contemporary dance at a studio in Brooklyn and perform whenever I can. I''m looking for someone who appreciates movement, isn''t afraid to dance in public, and understands that a good dance partner in life is even more important than one in the studio.',
        'Veterinarian who will definitely ask to see pictures of your pet within the first five minutes of meeting you. Animals are my life - I have a rescue dog named Mango who is objectively the best dog in NYC. I got into this field because I believe in treating all creatures with compassion and care. Looking for someone who loves animals, preferably has a pet, and doesn''t mind that I might come home smelling like dog occasionally.',
        'Scientist by day, aspiring comedian by night. I work in a biotech lab developing new treatments, which is fascinating but not exactly dinner conversation material. So I started doing open mics as a way to connect with normal humans about normal things. I''m looking for someone who can appreciate both a peer-reviewed journal and a well-timed punchline.',
        'Professor who promises not to lecture you - at least not on the first date. I teach literature at a small college in the city and I genuinely love what I do. There''s nothing better than watching a student connect with a text for the first time. Outside the classroom, I''m a regular person who likes good food, live music, and terrible reality TV. Looking for someone who reads but doesn''t judge my trashy guilty pleasures.',
