        'Therapist who won''t analyze you - much. I specialize in couples counseling, which gives me a pretty unique perspective on relationships. I know what works and what doesn''t, and I''m looking for something real. I believe in communication, vulnerability, and doing the work. But I also know how to turn off therapist mode and just be a person who wants to get to know you.',
        'Publicist with all the good party invites - and I''m looking for someone to bring as my plus one. I work with celebrities and brands, which means my job is basically professional socializing. I love the energy of events and I''m great at working a room. Looking for someone who can hold their own in a crowd, makes a great first impression, and doesn''t mind being my date to random industry events.',
        'Film editor and I''ll cut right to the chase - I''m looking for something real. I spend my days in a dark room cutting together stories, which is incredibly satisfying but also pretty solitary. I need someone who can drag me outside occasionally, who appreciates a good movie as much as I do, and who understands that sometimes the best version of a story requires patience and revision.',
        'Data scientist looking for chemistry that can''t be quantified. I spend my days building models and finding patterns in data, but I know that the best things in life can''t be reduced to numbers. I''m analytical by nature but romantic by choice. Looking for someone who appreciates logic but also believes in magic, whatever that means to them.',
        'Consultant traveling every week but worth the wait. I work for a big firm and I''m on a plane more often than I''m home. But I''ve got status on every airline and points at every hotel, so our vacation game will be strong. I''m looking for someone independent who has their own life but wants to merge itineraries eventually. Long-distance dating? I''ve got it down to a science.',
